rComments: Erin is one of the best profs I've had during my three years at uOttawa. Her lectures were captivating and fun to watch, and her assignments and tests were fair and covered course content evenly. She makes it known she cares about her students, and her participation points make it hard to fall behind. It's a decent amount of work but worth it!

Erin is a great prof, and this course will make you learn! However, it is a lot of work, so get ready to complete these assignments and weekly discussions. I personally think she was a harsh grader, but once you understand what she is looking for, you'll succeed. Not a bird class, so good luck!

Seriously the best prof. Erin couldn't be any more kind and approachable. She's a PhD candidate at the moment so she's very involved with all the material while also understanding the pressures of being a student. Very accommodating and accessible outside of class if you need anything. I really can't speak highly enough of her. TAKE THIS COURSE!!!!

AMAZING PROF. She really cares about her students and makes everything so easy for everyone. I can't stop recommending her. The only negative points is that her class can be very heavy: two weekly long lectures + lots of reading + discussion every week + two assignments + one group project + midterm + final (but can give extensions!!)

Professor Courtice is amazing. By far my favourite prof at UofO. She really, truly cares about her students, is so genuine, intellectually stimulating and easy to listen to during lectures. The assignments were actually enjoyable to do, and the grading was very fair. Can't recommend her enough!

Erin is the best!! This course was incredibly interesting and I can't recommend it enough. Its not a bird course but as long as you care and engage with the material it's not too hard. Had weekly readings and discussion groups which I thought I'd hate but they went super well! Tests are all take home essay type questions and 2 assignments this year

Each lecture was paired with a research article or two, all readings were super relevant and interesting! It's nice not having to pay for a textbook. Assignments and exams were writing dominant but creative and fun to do. Would highly recommend this course, the material is very interesting and informative!!

This was a very heavy course that took up A LOT of time but Erin is so dedicated to the subject. She really cares about her students and puts a lot of work into her material but this is definitely not a "bird course".

Erin is a great prof. She clearly cares about the subject matter she teaches. She seems to be invested in her students' success but expects you to rise to the challenge. Lots of writing. Expects you to participate.

Erin is kind and smart, but I'm not sure if this class was for me. She expected specific answers for broad questions on all assessments. The exams were long; the final is 4200 words. I think she is a good prof but she made it difficult to succeed in this course. However she is compassionate and available outside class to talk about anything.

great lectures, assignments that made the material easy to apply to life like making a playlist! a lot of technology but helped make it easy to contact the prof for help. plus opportunities for bonus points were much appreciated during covid

Erin is absolutely a kind and caring professor - you can tell she is very dedicated. However, the workload was way too excessive. Her lectures were long and so were the readings and constant assignments, and overall this course load took up double what all my other classes took.

Erin is an AMAZING prof! She had engaging lectures and her assignments/ midterms were very fair and had a lot of room for creativity - no memorization and regurgitation. She really cares about her students, she was so accommodating for mental health and especially during covid and very easy to get a hold. Very bright and genuine person!

Prof Courtice was incredibly helpful to me in the Fall Semester 2019; I was experiencing mental health issues and she went out of her way to make sure I was all caught up, even scheduling office hours for me outside of her usual times. The class was engaging and enjoyable! Would definitely recommend.

Professor Courtice is one of the sweetest professor's here at uOttawa. She truly does care about her students and she is always open for questions and help after class. Her class did not require a textbook and she posts all of her slides online but they are incomplete to get you to come to class. She made 830 classes really interesting!
she's a great teacher and seems to care about her students

Professor Courtice is by far the best prof I've had at uOttawa. She actually cares about student success, listens to feedback and actually implements it into the course. Not only is she super helpful but she also made the class very relevant and I always left each lesson learning something that I can apply in my daily life. Would 100% recommend.

Best Prof I have ever had at UOttawa, So engaging and interesting! She is also an amazing prof and is always available to chat and help you further understand the material. She really cares about her students and it shows! Also, course content is so eye opening and interesting 10/10 recomend

This is without a doubt my favourite class I've taken in all of undergrad; Professor Courtice is so kind, knowledgeable, and motivating. The course is also really interesting and well-organized, and I looked forward to every class and office hour. I hope I get the opportunity to be in her class again.
